of producing atRA and present with severe developmental defects (Niederreither et al, 1999). Conversely, mice lacking Aldh1a1 or Aldh1a3 survive fetal development, with phenotypes presenting postnatally (Dup&eacute; et al, 2003; Fan et al, 2003; Molotkov &amp; Duester, 2003). Thus, the biological plausibility that inhibition of ALDH1A2 will lead to decreased atRA in cells and tissues during development is strong.", "timestamp": "Mon Jun 08 15:35:09 +0000 2026"}